the focus of the mirror, whilst one<lb/>
painted black, would immediately<lb/>
indicate the elevation of temperature.<lb/>
Instance<lb/>
These facts have been known for<lb/>
some time, but there is another curious<lb/>
property of bodies, with regard to<lb/>
radiation, that has been only very<lb/>
lately discovered.<lb/>
Different bodies heated to the same<lb/>
temperature, give out radiant heat<lb/>
with very different degrees of quickness<lb/>
&amp; their power of emitting radiant heat.<lb/>
