            </del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">production</add> &amp; reflection of<lb/>
heat making rays. - If Heat<lb/>
passed from Body to body merely<lb/>
by simple contact or communication.<lb/>
The quantity of <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">cold</hi> air entering<lb/>
our rooms by different apertures<lb/>
would be as great as the quantity<lb/>
of Hot air conceived out of them,<lb/>
through the chimneys of <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">fire places</hi>-<lb/>
&amp; little or no elevation of temperature<lb/>
would be produced. -<lb/>
Radiant Heat, however passes through<lb/>
all currents of Air. - Its velocity is<lb/>
impeded by no perturbations, <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">&amp;</del>
            <lb/>
undulations, &amp; it is in a constant<lb/>
state of action &amp; of motion. -<lb/>
