- The production of Heat by the friction<lb/>
of solid Bodies, or by briskly rubbing<lb/>
them together, in a dry state, has been<lb/>
known from the earliest times, &amp;<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">amongst the most barbarous Nations</hi>. -<lb/>
